  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1030 mg
cuisine: Mexican
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tex-mex-chicken-with-mango-salsa-650ad03af209a4fa36352ef9
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a
pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, drain @Mango{4%oz} over a #small bowl{}, reserving juice;
roughly chop. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%oz}.
Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}.

To #bowl{} with mango juice, stir in @Tex-Mex Paste{1}, juice from half the
lime, and @water{2%tbsp}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine chopped mango, cilantro, scallions, and a
squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season with salt and @pepper{}.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%oz} dry with paper towels and season all over with
@Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If seasoning begins to burn before pork is cooked through, reduce heat
> to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least
~{5%minutes}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork; cook chicken until browned and cooked
> through, 4-6 minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes
> per side.

Return pan used for pork to medium-high heat. Add Tex-Mex paste mixture and
bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

> Use pan used for chicken or steak here.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with pork. Drizzle pork with pan sauce,
then garnish with mango salsa and @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tbsp}. Serve with
any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Thinly slice chicken or steak against the grain.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.